<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910701-0189</DOCNO><DOCID>910701-0189.</DOCID><HL>   Harsco Sells Defense Vehicles</HL><DATE>07/01/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C12</SO><CO>   HSC</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD)</IN><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)PENNSYLVANIA (PA)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   HARRISBURG, Pa. -- Harsco Corp. said that its BMY-CombatSystems division of its defense group has been awarded a U.S.contract for M-88A1 Recovery Vehicles valued at about $58million.   The industrial concern said the contract supports aforeign-military acquisition on behalf of a U.S. ally.Deliveries are to occur between May and November 1993.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>